9:
She knew about this World Flipper. 
She might also know about what 
happened on Challua's world.
18:
Rolan was hiding away a giant 
MARBLE? What was he thinking?
22:
This is a World Flipper. A link to other 
worlds.
26:
That thing from the stories Rolan used 
to tell...
29: The World Flipper is more than a story.
46:
Synchronization complete.
...Unfortunately, Light, your world is 
not in this region.
51:
Five regions left... It's not easy, seeking 
a world in the sky.
53:
There's also the matter of my form... 
How will I return to being human?
56: Tiger. Where are you headed now?
60:
Who knows? I lived for revenge. Now 
that that's over, I don't have any 
direction.
65: My name is Stella. What is yours?
74:
Oh yeah, we never introduced 
ourselves. I'm Alk.
90: Like the cloud? That's kind of cute.
94:
Rolan said it's 'cause I'm white and 
fluffy. He was a kid all right—through 
and through.
96:
But... I wouldn't trade this name for the 
world.
102: Nimbus, why don't you come with us?
105:
Those seven regions contain 
countless worlds. Worlds vastly 
different from this one.
107: You do not have to stay here.
109:
I believe your world is out there. 
So, um...
114:
You're the only beastfolk around these 
parts, right? Don't you want to find out 
where you came from?
126:
You, uh, aren't the most convincing 
speaker.
136:
Hah. Why do I always attract the 
weirdest people?
138:
Well, better than bein' dead, I guess. 
Sure, I'll come along for the ride.
162:
You owe us nothing, Nadir. 
You did your best.
177:
Your brothers and sisters. 
Were they okay?
186:
Good. Then stay here and keep them 
that way. Don't slip up.
191:
Got it! Sorry... and thanks for 
everything!
196:
I'm headin' out, Rolan. 
Let's see if those stories you used to 
tell have a happy ending.
